    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 1993 Mazda RX-7 FD is a museum-grade specimen featuring the iconic sequential twin-turbocharged 13B-REW rotary engine. Meticulously maintained, the drivetrain retains factory compression specs across all rotor faces, paired with a precise 5-speed manual transmission and a Torsen limited-slip differential. The chassis exhibits zero fatigue, benefiting from a double-wishbone suspension setup that remains tight and responsive. This unit is free of typical vacuum line degradation or heat-cycle fatigue, featuring an upgraded aluminum radiator for enhanced thermal management. A rare, unmodified example with a flawless finish and an interior showing zero bolster wear\u2014truly a turn-key investment for the discerning collector.",
